        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 8:04AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 804 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
McRae, or 10 miles south of Searcy, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newport...                        Oil Trough...
Shoffner...                       Thida...
Bradford...                       Stegall...
Heffington...                     Amagon...
Grubbs...                         Judsonia...
Fitzhugh...                       Worden...
Kensett...                        Hurricane Lake WMA...
Velvet Ridge...                   Bald Knob...
Plainview in White County...      Olyphant...
Augusta...                        Ingleside...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
